@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@authToken = {{login.response.body.data.token}}

### Auth - Login
# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@example.com",
  "password": "change-me-strongly"
}

### Users - List (pagination + sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?page=1&limit=10&sort_by=name&sort_order=DESC
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Users - Invalid Sort (Should fail with 400)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?page=1&limit=10&sort_by=name
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Roles - List (pagination + sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/roles?page=1&limit=10&sort_by=name&sort_order=ASC
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Permissions - List (pagination + sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/permissions?page=1&limit=10&sort_by=name&sort_order=ASC
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Measurements - List (pagination + sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/measurements?study_instance_uid=1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2&page=1&limit=10&sort_by=label&sort_order=ASC
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Viewer State - List (pagination + sorting)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v1/viewer-state?study_instance_uid=1.2.840.10008.5.1.4.1.1.2&page=1&limit=10&sort_by=mode&sort_order=ASC
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Example (curl)
curl -s "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/users?page=1&limit=10&sort_by=name&sort_order=desc" -H "Authorization: Bearer ${TOKEN}" | jq

### Expected Response Shape
{
  "data": [ /* array of objects */ ],
  "meta": {
    "total": 0,
    "page": 1,
    "limit": 10,
    "last_page": 0,
    "sort_by": "created_at",
    "sort_order": "ASC"
  }
}

### Usage Notes
- Default ordering is always `created_at ASC` unless a whitelisted `sort_by` is provided.
- `sort_by` is validated against a whitelist to prevent SQL injection and return a 400 Bad Request if invalid.
- Use global `ValidationPipe` with `transform: true`, `whitelist: true`, `forbidNonWhitelisted: true` to enable DTO validation.

